## Example 2: Student Record System

A university system where student grades must be 0–100. GPA is auto-calculated and read-only.

**File: `student/record.go`**
```go
package student

import "fmt"

type Record struct {
    Name       string    // Exported
    RollNumber int       // Exported
    marks      [5]float64 // Unexported: only this package can set marks
    gpa        float64    // Unexported: auto-calculated, read-only from outside
}

// Private helper — only callable within the 'student' package
func (r *Record) calculateGPA() {
    total := 0.0
    for _, m := range r.marks {
        total += m
    }
    r.gpa = total / 50.0  // GPA on 10-point scale
}

func NewRecord(name string, roll int) *Record {
    return &Record{
        Name:       name,
        RollNumber: roll,
    }
}

// SetMarks validates input and auto-recalculates GPA
func (r *Record) SetMarks(subject int, mark float64) bool {
    if subject < 0 || subject >= 5 || mark < 0 || mark > 100 {
        fmt.Println("ERROR: Invalid subject index or marks out of range (0-100)!")
        return false
    }
    r.marks[subject] = mark
    r.calculateGPA()  // Auto-update GPA whenever marks change
    return true
}

// Read-only getters
func (r *Record) GetGPA() float64           { return r.gpa }
func (r *Record) GetMarks(subject int) float64 {
    if subject >= 0 && subject < 5 {
        return r.marks[subject]
    }
    return -1
}

func (r *Record) DisplayReport() {
    fmt.Printf("\n--- Student Report Card ---\n")
    fmt.Printf("Name: %s | Roll: %d\n", r.Name, r.RollNumber)
    for i := 0; i < 5; i++ {
        fmt.Printf("Subject %d: %.1f\n", i+1, r.marks[i])
    }
    fmt.Printf("GPA: %.2f/10.0\n", r.gpa)
}
```

**Key Takeaway:** GPA is completely read-only from outside. It auto-updates whenever marks change. Nobody can manually set `gpa = 10.0`.

